gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Knicks 112, Timberwolves 106
gameRecap.excerpt: The Knicks defeated the Timberwolves, 112-106. Julius Randle led the way for the Knicks with 39 points (12 in the fourth quarter) and nine rebounds, while Jalen Brunson added 16 points and a career-high 14 assists in the victory. OG Anunoby notched 17 points, six rebounds, and three 3PM for the Knicks in his debut. Anthony Edwards (35 points, four 3PM) and Karl-Anthony Towns (29 points, three 3PM) combined for 64 points for the Timberwolves in the losing effort. The Knicks snap a three-game losing streak as they improve to 18-15 on the season, while the Timberwolves fall to 24-8.
